{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Documentation Sync",
  "description": "Listens to Python source files and configuration changes to automatically update project documentation in README and docs folder.\nOrganize any implementation md files generated, or test scripts and/or loose documentation, and update DOCUMENTATION_APPENDIX_CURRENT_FILES.md for the system to know which and where all the relevant and up to date documentations are.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered",
    "patterns": [
      "*.py",
      "config/*.py",
      "config/*.json",
      "tools/*.py",
      "utils/*.py",
      "suppliers/**/*.py",
      "langraph_integration/*.py",
      "langgraph_integration/*.py",
      "monitoring/*.py",
      "tests/*.py",
      "requirements.txt",
      "pyproject.toml"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Source files have been modified in this Python project. Please analyze the changes and update the documentation accordingly. Focus on:\n\n1. Update the main README.md file if core functionality has changed\n2. Update relevant documentation in the /docs folder for specific components\n3. Update configuration documentation if config files changed\n4. Update setup/installation instructions if requirements changed\n5. Place any generated md files for specific implemetnations in \"improvement\" folder,  with proper organization ( e.g: clear folder names based on implementations.)\n6. Place any test scripts generate for implemenations in \"test\" folder , proper organizations (e.g: clear folder name based on tests and/or implementation ) \n7. archive all the outdate files in the respective foders\n\nPlease review the changed files and provide comprehensive documentation updates that accurately reflect the current state of the codebase."
  }
}